      "span_text": "The nerve abducens innervates the lateral rectus extraocular muscle and is responsible for horizontal conjugate gaze.  Certain authors have suggested a downward displacement of the nerve due to increased intracranial pressure and nerve ischemia, such as in the case of cerebral edema. 4,  However, this disorder, and especially cerebral edema, usually supposes a more complex clinical picture."
